// CONTROL STATEMENTS

LOOP CONTROL:
	ASSERT:

cat test1.py 
#!/usr/bin/python

i = int(input('Enter a no smaller than 10: '))
assert i<10, "Entered by user is wrong!!! Please try different no.."
print("Entered by user is: ", i)

O/P:

./test1.py 
Enter a no smaller than 10: 2
('Entered by user is: ', 2)

./test1.py 
Enter a no smaller than 10: 11
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "./test1.py", line 4, in <module>
    assert i<10, "Entered by user is wrong!!! Please try different no.."
AssertionError: Entered by user is wrong!!! Please try different no..
